(1, '{\"en\":\"2-Ethyl Hexanol\",\"id\":\"2-Etil Hexanol\"}', '2905.16.20', '104-76-7', 'products/nL0yp8NR3ipcRZDvw3bo3Fu7BJhb5BmfwAc3D2br.jpg', '{\"en\":\"2-Ethylhexanol has one primary hydroxyl group. It is a colorless liquid. 2- Ethylhexanol is widely used in the production of dioctyl phthalate (vinyl applications), acrylates, 2-ethylhexyl nitrate, lubrication oil additives, mining chemicals, special plasticizers, herbicides and ester oils (non-vinyl application areas).\",\"id\":\"2-Etilheksanol memiliki satu gugus hidroksil primer. Bentuknya berupa cairan tak berwarna. 2-Etilheksanol banyak digunakan dalam produksi dioktil ftalat (aplikasi vinil), akrilat, 2-etilheksil nitrat, aditif oli pelumas, bahan kimia pertambangan, plasticizer khusus, herbisida, dan minyak ester (aplikasi non-vinil).\"}', '{\"en\":\"The production of the plasticizer diester bis(2-ethylhexyl) phthalate (DEHP) which is commonly used on the production of PVC is the main application of 2-ethylhexanol. Esters of 2-ethylhexanol often have emollient properties because it is a fatty alcohol. It can also be applied for the production of DOP, DOTP, TOTM\",\"id\":\"Produksi plasticizer diester bis(2-etilheksil) ftalat (DEHP) yang umum digunakan dalam produksi PVC merupakan aplikasi utama 2-etilheksanol. Ester 2-etilheksanol seringkali memiliki sifat emolien karena merupakan alkohol lemak. Ester ini juga dapat digunakan untuk produksi DOP, DOTP, dan TOTM.\"}', '{\"en\":\"2-Ethyl Hexanol\",\"id\":\"2-Etil Hexanol\"}', '{\"en\":\"paint, ink, and coating\",\"id\":\"cat, tinta, dan pelapis\"}', '{\"en\":\"The industrial production of 2-ethylhexanol is by a three-step process involving the aldol self-condensation of n butyraldehyde followed by dehydration and hydrogenation. The n-butyraldehyde was originally obtained\\r\\nfrom acetaldehyde via ethylene but this has been superseded by the oxo process from propylene.\",\"id\":\"The industrial production of 2-ethylhexanol is by a three-step process involving the aldol self-condensation of n butyraldehyde followed by dehydration and hydrogenation. The n-butyraldehyde was originally obtained\\r\\nfrom acetaldehyde via ethylene but this has been superseded by the oxo process from propylene.\"}', '2025-07-08 14:16:37', '2025-07-09 02:49:08'),
(3, '{\"en\":\"2-Ethylhexyl Acrylate\",\"id\":\"2-Etilheksil Akrilat\"}', '2916.12.90', '103-11-7', 'products/4TeAVlIjtjiKKKH8Xgko3ck6kywLcrRV7DmoMbkh.jpg', '{\"en\":\"2-ethylhexyl acrylate is an acrylate monomer with the formula of CH2=CHCOOC8H17   (C11H20O2). 2-Ehtlyhexyl Acrylate has the characteristic of liquid, colorless, and has an unpleasant acrylic odor. 2-EHA is not soluble in water but soluble in alcohols and ethers.  2 ethylhexyl acrylate is not a very flammable liquid with a flashpoint between 75 \\u2013 90\\u00b0 C.\",\"id\":\"2-etilheksil akrilat adalah monomer akrilat dengan rumus CH2 = CHCOOC8H17 ( C11H20O2   ). 2-Etilheksil Akrilat memiliki karakteristik cair, tidak berwarna, dan berbau akrilik yang  tidak sedap. 2-EHA tidak larut dalam air tetapi larut dalam alkohol dan eter. 2-etilheksil akrilat bukanlah cairan yang mudah terbakar dengan titik nyala antara 75 \\u2013 90\\u00b0C.\"}', '{\"en\":\"For paint and coatings, 2-Ethylhexyl Acrylate owns characteristics such as water resistanant, flexibility on low temperatures, durability sunlight resistant, and good weathering.\",\"id\":\"2-EHA juga dapat diaplikasikan untuk berbagai keperluan atau industri seperti modifikasi serat, modifikasi kain, aditif pemrosesan, pelapis, manufaktur homopolimer, manufaktur kopolimer, aditif pemrosesan kulit.\"}', '{\"en\":\"2-Ethylhexyl Acrylate\",\"id\":\"2-Etilheksil Akrilat\"}', '{\"en\":\"Plastic and Polymers\",\"id\":\"Plastik dan Polimer\"}', '{\"en\":\"For paint and coatings, 2-Ethylhexyl Acrylate owns characteristics such as water resistanant, flexibility on low temperatures, durability sunlight resistant, and good weathering.\",\"id\":\"2-etilheksil akrilat adalah monomer akrilat dengan rumus CH2 = CHCOOC8H17 ( C11H20O2   ). 2-Etilheksil Akrilat memiliki karakteristik cair, tidak berwarna, dan berbau akrilik yang  tidak sedap. 2-EHA tidak larut dalam air tetapi larut dalam alkohol dan eter. 2-etilheksil akrilat bukanlah cairan yang mudah terbakar dengan titik nyala antara 75 \\u2013 90\\u00b0C.\"}', '2025-07-08 20:25:28', '2025-07-09 02:50:16'),
(4, '{\"en\":\"Acesulfame Potassium\",\"id\":\"Acesulfam Kalium\"}', '2934.99.00', '55589-62-3', 'products/toGaqCozsdE9Nm2NoH3JZrofQdDD79jvHQV0QZwx.jpg', '{\"en\":\"Acesulfame potassium, also known by ace K, acesulfame K, is an artificial sweetener used in foods. It is almost 200 times sweeter than sugar and is also found not to change blood insulin levels. Thus, it is commonly called as diabetic sweetener. Acesulfame K is usually mixed with other artificial sweeteners. The other two sweeteners masks the bitterness of acesulfame lave in our mouth. In its solid form, acesulfame-K is highly stable at room temperature, even in the presence of light. When in solution, its stability is dependent on pH and temperature. Glycaemic index of acesulfame potassium is zero and it is one of the cheapest sweeteners.\",\"id\":\"Kalium asesulfam, juga dikenal sebagai asesulfam-K, adalah pemanis buatan yang digunakan dalam makanan. Asesulfam-K hampir 200 kali lebih manis daripada gula dan juga terbukti tidak mengubah kadar insulin darah. Oleh karena itu, asesulfam-K umumnya disebut sebagai pemanis diabetes. Asesulfam-K biasanya dicampur dengan pemanis buatan lainnya. Dua pemanis lainnya menutupi rasa pahit asesulfam-K di mulut kita. Dalam bentuk padatnya, asesulfam-K sangat stabil pada suhu ruangan, bahkan di bawah cahaya. Dalam larutan, stabilitasnya bergantung pada pH dan suhu. Indeks glikemik asesulfam-K adalah nol dan merupakan salah satu pemanis termurah.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Used in candies, ice cream, jellies, jams and beverages, etc. Acesulfame potassium is a calorie-free sweetener that replaces sugar in foods and beverages to add sweetness without adding extra calories.\",\"id\":\"Digunakan dalam permen, es krim, jeli, selai dan minuman, dll. Kalium asesulfam merupakan pemanis bebas kalori yang menggantikan gula dalam makanan dan minuman untuk menambah rasa manis tanpa menambah kalori ekstra.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acesulfame Potassium\",\"id\":\"Acesulfam Kalium\"}', '{\"en\":\"Food Ingridients\",\"id\":\"Bahan Makanan\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acesulfame potassium, also known by ace K, acesulfame K, is an artificial sweetener used in foods. It is almost 200 times sweeter than sugar and is also found not to change blood insulin levels. Thus, it is commonly called as diabetic sweetener. Acesulfame K is usually mixed with other artificial sweeteners. The other two sweeteners masks the bitterness of acesulfame lave in our mouth. In its solid form, acesulfame-K is highly stable at room temperature, even in the presence of light. When in solution, its stability is dependent on pH and temperature. Glycaemic index of acesulfame potassium is zero and it is one of the cheapest sweeteners.\",\"id\":\"Digunakan dalam permen, es krim, jeli, selai dan minuman, dll. Kalium asesulfam merupakan pemanis bebas kalori yang menggantikan gula dalam makanan dan minuman untuk menambah rasa manis tanpa menambah kalori ekstra.\"}', '2025-07-08 20:25:46', '2025-07-09 02:52:15'),
(5, '{\"en\":\"Acrylic Acid (99.5%) - China\",\"id\":\"Asam Akrilik (99,5%) - Cina\"}', '2916.11.00', '79-10-7', 'products/preFDdHnTMOcmSw1UHf4aJglC4pZZVz7g0EkAUeI.jpg', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid is an unsaturated carboxylic acid, with the formula CH2=CHCO2H. This clear and colourless liquid has a characteristic acrid odour. As it contains a polar carboxylic acid functional group, it is able to dissolve in water and is miscible with relatively polar organic compounds such as alcohols, ethers, and chloroform. Acrylic acid is air and water sensitive as it reacts readily with free radicals and electrophilic or nucleophilic agents. It may polymerise in the presence of acids, alkalis, amines, peroxides, and iron salts. Prolonged exposure to heat or exposure of light can also cause polymerisation. If confined, the polymerisation of acrylic acid can lead to explosion even at room temperature. It is corrosive to metals and tissues.\\r\\n\\r\\nAcrylic acid can be used in the form of free acids, ammonium and alkali salts in many different applications such as thickeners, dispersing agents, flocculants, wetting agents, coatings, textile finishes protective colloids for stabilizing emulsions and polymer dispersions. It readily undergoes additional reactions with a wide variety of organic and inorganic compounds, which makes it a very useful feedstock for the production of many low molecular compounds. For instance, acrylic acid can be used to produce derivatives of propionic acid with water, alcohols, amines, halogens and chlorinated hydrocarbons. It can also react with other substances to produce unsaturated fatty acids, heterocyclic compounds and Diels-Alder addition products.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs it polymerises with explosive violence, it can only be shipped after being stabilised by an inhibitor such as hydroquinone. The removal of the stabilizer is not usually necessary, since its action can be compensated for by adding an excessive initiator.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilat adalah asam karboksilat tak jenuh dengan rumus CH2 = CHCO2H . Cairan bening dan tak berwarna ini memiliki bau tajam yang khas. Karena mengandung gugus fungsi asam karboksilat polar, asam akrilat dapat larut dalam air dan dapat bercampur dengan senyawa organik yang relatif polar seperti alkohol, eter, dan kloroform. Asam akrilat sensitif terhadap udara dan air karena mudah bereaksi dengan radikal bebas dan agen elektrofilik atau nukleofilik. Asam akrilat dapat berpolimerasi dengan adanya asam, alkali, amina, peroksida, dan garam besi. Paparan panas atau cahaya yang terlalu lama juga dapat menyebabkan polimerisasi. Jika terkurung, polimerisasi asam akrilat dapat menyebabkan ledakan bahkan pada suhu ruangan. Asam akrilat bersifat korosif terhadap logam dan jaringan.\\r\\n\\r\\nAsam akrilik dapat digunakan dalam bentuk asam bebas, garam amonium dan alkali dalam berbagai aplikasi seperti pengental, zat pendispersi, flokulan, zat pembasah, pelapis, pelapis tekstil, koloid pelindung untuk menstabilkan emulsi dan dispersi polimer. Asam akrilik mudah mengalami reaksi tambahan dengan berbagai macam senyawa organik dan anorganik, yang menjadikannya bahan baku yang sangat berguna untuk produksi banyak senyawa molekul rendah. Misalnya, asam akrilik dapat digunakan untuk menghasilkan turunan asam propionat dengan air, alkohol, amina, halogen dan hidrokarbon terklorinasi. Asam akrilik juga dapat bereaksi dengan zat lain untuk menghasilkan asam lemak tak jenuh, senyawa heterosiklik dan produk adisi Diels-Alder.\\r\\n\\r\\nKarena berpolimerisasi dengan kekuatan eksplosif, zat ini hanya dapat dikirim setelah distabilkan oleh inhibitor seperti hidrokuinon. Penghilangan zat penstabil biasanya tidak diperlukan, karena efeknya dapat dikompensasi dengan menambahkan inisiator berlebih.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid is primarily used as starting material for preparation of chemicals such as methyl acrylate, ethyl acrylate, butyl acrylate and 2-ethylhexyl acrylate. These monomers are polymerised, and are used in hygiene products with superabsorbent resins such as disposable diapers, in water-based paints and coatings, construction adhesives and pressure-sensitive adhesives, coatings for textiles, wood and paper, in leather finishing etc.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey also function mainly as an intermediate for the production of acrylate esters which are used to produce plastic additives, adhesives, coatings, textiles and paints. However, due to environmental concerns, their production was stopped.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilik terutama digunakan sebagai bahan awal untuk persiapan bahan kimia seperti metil akrilat, etil akrilat, butil akrilat, dan 2-etilheksil akrilat. Monomer-monomer ini dipolimerisasi, dan digunakan dalam produk-produk higienis dengan resin superabsorben seperti popok sekali pakai, dalam cat dan pelapis berbasis air, perekat konstruksi dan perekat peka tekanan, pelapis untuk tekstil, kayu dan kertas, dalam pelapisan kulit, dll.\\r\\n\\r\\nMereka juga berfungsi terutama sebagai perantara untuk produksi ester akrilat yang digunakan untuk memproduksi aditif plastik, perekat, pelapis, tekstil, dan cat. Namun, karena masalah lingkungan, produksinya dihentikan.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic Acid (99.5%) - China\",\"id\":\"Asam Akrilik (99,5%) - Cina\"}', '{\"en\":\"Paint, Ink, Coating, and Water Treatment Chemical\",\"id\":\"Cat, Tinta, Pelapis dan Bahan Kimia Pengolahan Air\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid is an unsaturated carboxylic acid, with the formula CH2=CHCO2H. This clear and colourless liquid has a characteristic acrid odour. As it contains a polar carboxylic acid functional group, it is able to dissolve in water and is miscible with relatively polar organic compounds such as alcohols, ethers, and chloroform. Acrylic acid is air and water sensitive as it reacts readily with free radicals and electrophilic or nucleophilic agents. It may polymerise in the presence of acids, alkalis, amines, peroxides, and iron salts. Prolonged exposure to heat or exposure of light can also cause polymerisation. If confined, the polymerisation of acrylic acid can lead to explosion even at room temperature. It is corrosive to metals and tissues.\\r\\n\\r\\nAcrylic acid can be used in the form of free acids, ammonium and alkali salts in many different applications such as thickeners, dispersing agents, flocculants, wetting agents, coatings, textile finishes protective colloids for stabilizing emulsions and polymer dispersions. It readily undergoes additional reactions with a wide variety of organic and inorganic compounds, which makes it a very useful feedstock for the production of many low molecular compounds. For instance, acrylic acid can be used to produce derivatives of propionic acid with water, alcohols, amines, halogens and chlorinated hydrocarbons. It can also react with other substances to produce unsaturated fatty acids, heterocyclic compounds and Diels-Alder addition products.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs it polymerises with explosive violence, it can only be shipped after being stabilised by an inhibitor such as hydroquinone. The removal of the stabilizer is not usually necessary, since its action can be compensated for by adding an excessive initiator.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilat adalah asam karboksilat tak jenuh dengan rumus CH2 = CHCO2H . Cairan bening dan tak berwarna ini memiliki bau tajam yang khas. Karena mengandung gugus fungsi asam karboksilat polar, asam akrilat dapat larut dalam air dan dapat bercampur dengan senyawa organik yang relatif polar seperti alkohol, eter, dan kloroform. Asam akrilat sensitif terhadap udara dan air karena mudah bereaksi dengan radikal bebas dan agen elektrofilik atau nukleofilik. Asam akrilat dapat berpolimerasi dengan adanya asam, alkali, amina, peroksida, dan garam besi. Paparan panas atau cahaya yang terlalu lama juga dapat menyebabkan polimerisasi. Jika terkurung, polimerisasi asam akrilat dapat menyebabkan ledakan bahkan pada suhu ruangan. Asam akrilat bersifat korosif terhadap logam dan jaringan.\\r\\n\\r\\nAsam akrilik dapat digunakan dalam bentuk asam bebas, garam amonium dan alkali dalam berbagai aplikasi seperti pengental, zat pendispersi, flokulan, zat pembasah, pelapis, pelapis tekstil, koloid pelindung untuk menstabilkan emulsi dan dispersi polimer. Asam akrilik mudah mengalami reaksi tambahan dengan berbagai macam senyawa organik dan anorganik, yang menjadikannya bahan baku yang sangat berguna untuk produksi banyak senyawa molekul rendah. Misalnya, asam akrilik dapat digunakan untuk menghasilkan turunan asam propionat dengan air, alkohol, amina, halogen dan hidrokarbon terklorinasi. Asam akrilik juga dapat bereaksi dengan zat lain untuk menghasilkan asam lemak tak jenuh, senyawa heterosiklik dan produk adisi Diels-Alder.\\r\\n\\r\\nKarena berpolimerisasi dengan kekuatan eksplosif, zat ini hanya dapat dikirim setelah distabilkan oleh inhibitor seperti hidrokuinon. Penghilangan zat penstabil biasanya tidak diperlukan, karena efeknya dapat dikompensasi dengan menambahkan inisiator berlebih.\"}', '2025-07-08 20:26:08', '2025-07-09 02:54:14'),
(6, '{\"en\":\"Acrylic Acid (Glacial) - China\",\"id\":\"Asam Akrilik (Glasial) - Cina\"}', '2916.11.00', '79-10-7', 'products/WpZ9nDajJVWBV1Zel6eOLQocXK5tbbMMeYLwBF94.jpg', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid, having the chemical formula CH2=CHCO2H, is an unsaturated carboxylic acid. This clear and colorless liquid is characterized by its acrid odor. Due to the presence of a polar carboxylic acid functional group, it exhibits solubility in water and miscibility with relatively polar organic compounds like alcohols, ethers, and chloroform. Acrylic acid is sensitive to air and water, readily reacting with free radicals and electrophilic or nucleophilic agents. Polymerization can occur in the presence of acids, alkalis, amines, peroxides, and iron salts. Prolonged exposure to heat or light can also induce polymerization, and if confined, it may lead to an explosion even at room temperature. The corrosive nature of acrylic acid extends to metals and tissues. Utilized in various forms, including free acids, ammonium, and alkali salts, acrylic acid finds applications as thickeners, dispersing agents, flocculants, wetting agents, coatings, textile finishes, and protective colloids for stabilizing emulsions and polymer dispersions. Its versatility is evident in its participation in additional reactions with a broad range of organic and inorganic compounds, making it a valuable feedstock for producing numerous low molecular compounds. For example, acrylic acid can be employed in the production of derivatives of propionic acid involving water, alcohols, amines, halogens, and chlorinated hydrocarbons. Additionally, it can react with other substances to generate unsaturated fatty acids, heterocyclic compounds, and Diels-Alder addition products. Given its tendency to polymerize explosively, acrylic acid must be stabilized with an inhibitor like hydroquinone before shipping. The removal of the stabilizer is typically unnecessary, as its effects can be compensated for by adding an excess initiator.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilat, dengan rumus kimia CH2=CHCO2H, adalah asam karboksilat tak jenuh. Cairan bening dan tak berwarna ini memiliki bau yang menyengat. Karena adanya gugus fungsi asam karboksilat polar, asam akrilat larut dalam air dan dapat bercampur dengan senyawa organik yang relatif polar seperti alkohol, eter, dan kloroform. Asam akrilat sensitif terhadap udara dan air, mudah bereaksi dengan radikal bebas dan agen elektrofilik atau nukleofilik. Polimerisasi dapat terjadi dengan adanya asam, alkali, amina, peroksida, dan garam besi. Paparan panas atau cahaya yang terlalu lama juga dapat menginduksi polimerisasi, dan jika disimpan dalam ruangan, dapat menyebabkan ledakan bahkan pada suhu ruangan. Sifat korosif asam akrilat juga dapat meluas hingga ke logam dan jaringan. Dimanfaatkan dalam berbagai bentuk, termasuk asam bebas, amonium, dan garam alkali, asam akrilat dapat diaplikasikan sebagai pengental, zat pendispersi, flokulan, zat pembasah, pelapis, pelapis tekstil, dan koloid pelindung untuk menstabilkan emulsi dan dispersi polimer. Keserbagunaannya terbukti dari partisipasinya dalam reaksi tambahan dengan beragam senyawa organik dan anorganik, menjadikannya bahan baku yang berharga untuk menghasilkan berbagai senyawa molekul rendah. Misalnya, asam akrilat dapat digunakan dalam produksi turunan asam propionat yang melibatkan air, alkohol, amina, halogen, dan hidrokarbon terklorinasi. Selain itu, asam akrilat dapat bereaksi dengan zat lain untuk menghasilkan asam lemak tak jenuh, senyawa heterosiklik, dan produk adisi Diels-Alder. Mengingat kecenderungannya untuk berpolimerisasi secara eksplosif, asam akrilat harus distabilkan dengan inhibitor seperti hidrokuinon sebelum pengiriman. Penghilangan zat penstabil biasanya tidak diperlukan, karena efeknya dapat dikompensasi dengan menambahkan inisiator berlebih.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid serves as a key raw material for creating various chemicals like methyl acrylate, ethyl acrylate, butyl acrylate, and 2-ethylhexyl acrylate. These chemicals, once polymerized, find applications in hygiene products like disposable diapers, water-based paints, construction adhesives, pressure-sensitive adhesives, and coatings for textiles, wood, and paper. Additionally, they play a crucial role as intermediates in the production of acrylate esters, essential for making plastic additives, adhesives, coatings, textiles, and paints. However, environmental concerns have led to the discontinuation of their production.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilat berfungsi sebagai bahan baku utama untuk pembuatan berbagai bahan kimia seperti metil akrilat, etil akrilat, butil akrilat, dan 2-etilheksil akrilat. Setelah terpolimerisasi, bahan kimia ini dapat diaplikasikan dalam produk-produk higienis seperti popok sekali pakai, cat berbahan dasar air, perekat konstruksi, perekat peka tekanan, dan pelapis untuk tekstil, kayu, dan kertas. Selain itu, asam akrilat berperan penting sebagai zat antara dalam produksi ester akrilat, yang penting untuk pembuatan aditif plastik, perekat, pelapis, tekstil, dan cat. Namun, kekhawatiran lingkungan telah menyebabkan penghentian produksinya.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic Acid (Glacial) - China\",\"id\":\"Asam Akrilik (Glasial) - Cina\"}', '{\"en\":\"Paint, Ink, and Coating\",\"id\":\"Cat, Tinta, dan Pelapis\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid serves as a key raw material for creating various chemicals like methyl acrylate, ethyl acrylate, butyl acrylate, and 2-ethylhexyl acrylate. These chemicals, once polymerized, find applications in hygiene products like disposable diapers, water-based paints, construction adhesives, pressure-sensitive adhesives, and coatings for textiles, wood, and paper. Additionally, they play a crucial role as intermediates in the production of acrylate esters, essential for making plastic additives, adhesives, coatings, textiles, and paints. However, environmental concerns have led to the discontinuation of their production.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilat, dengan rumu