(8, '{\"en\":\"Acrylic Acid (Industrial) - India\",\"id\":\"Asam Akrilik (Industri) - India\"}', '2916.11.00', '79-10-7', 'products/HBTckdyixXh7oymHfIYhbEzQnI6DduWN3PEZLJUp.jpg', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid, characterized by its unsaturated carboxylic acid structure (CH2=CHCO2H), presents as a clear, odorless liquid. It exhibits distinct solubility in water owing to its polar carboxylic acid functional group and mixes well with moderately polar organic compounds like alcohols, ethers, and chloroform. However, its sensitivity to air and water makes it highly reactive with free radicals, electrophilic or nucleophilic agents. Under specific conditions such as exposure to heat, light, or certain chemicals, acrylic acid tends to undergo polymerization, sometimes explosively, even at room temperature. This compound also displays corrosive properties towards metals and tissues.In various applications, acrylic acid finds use in multiple forms, including free acids, ammonium, and alkali salts. It serves diverse purposes such as thickening agents, dispersants, flocculants, wetting agents, coatings, and textile finishes. Its reactivity with a wide array of organic and inorganic compounds makes it a valuable source material for producing various lower molecular weight compounds. For instance, through reactions with water, alcohols, amines, halogens, and chlorinated hydrocarbons, acrylic acid can generate derivatives of propionic a\\r\\n\\r\\ncid. Additionally, it participates in reactions leading to unsaturated fatty acids, heterocyclic compounds, and Diels-Alder addition products.\\r\\n\\r\\nDue to its tendency to explosively polymerize, acrylic acid requires stabilization using inhibitors like hydroquinone before shipping. Typically, there\'s no need to remove the stabilizer as its effect can be balanced by adding an excessive initiator.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilik, yang dicirikan oleh struktur asam karboksilat tak jenuhnya (CH2=CHCO2H), berbentuk cairan bening dan tidak berbau. Asam akrilik menunjukkan kelarutan yang jelas dalam air karena gugus fungsi asam karboksilatnya yang polar dan bercampur dengan baik dengan senyawa organik yang cukup polar seperti alkohol, eter, dan kloroform. Namun, kepekaannya terhadap udara dan air membuatnya sangat reaktif dengan radikal bebas, agen elektrofilik atau nukleofilik. Dalam kondisi tertentu seperti paparan panas, cahaya, atau bahan kimia tertentu, asam akrilik cenderung mengalami polimerisasi, terkadang meledak, bahkan pada suhu ruangan. Senyawa ini juga menunjukkan sifat korosif terhadap logam dan jaringan. Dalam berbagai aplikasi, asam akrilik digunakan dalam berbagai bentuk, termasuk asam bebas, amonium, dan garam alkali. Asam akrilik memiliki beragam tujuan seperti bahan pengental, dispersan, flokulan, bahan pembasah, pelapis, dan pelapis tekstil. Reaktivitasnya dengan beragam senyawa organik dan anorganik menjadikannya bahan sumber yang berharga untuk menghasilkan berbagai senyawa dengan berat molekul rendah. Misalnya, melalui reaksi dengan air, alkohol, amina, halogen, dan hidrokarbon terklorinasi, asam akrilik dapat menghasilkan turunan asam propionat.\\r\\n\\r\\nSelain itu, ia berpartisipasi dalam reaksi yang menghasilkan asam lemak tak jenuh, senyawa heterosiklik, dan produk adisi Diels-Alder.\\r\\n\\r\\nKarena kecenderungannya untuk berpolimerisasi secara eksplosif, asam akrilik memerlukan stabilisasi menggunakan inhibitor seperti hidrokuinon sebelum pengiriman. Umumnya, penstabil tidak perlu dihilangkan karena efeknya dapat diimbangi dengan menambahkan inisiator berlebih.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid monomers, when copolymerized, find application in wastewater treatment, particularly in the flocculation of mineral ore fines, wastewater treatment, and the remediation of sewage.\",\"id\":\"Monomer asam akrilik, ketika dikopolimerisasi, dapat diaplikasikan dalam pengolahan air limbah, terutama pada flokulasi bijih mineral halus, pengolahan air limbah, dan remediasi limbah.\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic Acid (Industrial) - India\",\"id\":\"Asam Akrilik (Industri) - India\"}', '{\"en\":\"Water Treatment Chemicals\",\"id\":\"Bahan Kimia Pengolahan Air\"}', '{\"en\":\"Acrylic acid, characterized by its unsaturated carboxylic acid structure (CH2=CHCO2H), presents as a clear, odorless liquid. It exhibits distinct solubility in water owing to its polar carboxylic acid functional group and mixes well with moderately polar organic compounds like alcohols, ethers, and chloroform. However, its sensitivity to air and water makes it highly reactive with free radicals, electrophilic or nucleophilic agents. Under specific conditions such as exposure to heat, light, or certain chemicals, acrylic acid tends to undergo polymerization, sometimes explosively, even at room temperature. This compound also displays corrosive properties towards metals and tissues.In various applications, acrylic acid finds use in multiple forms, including free acids, ammonium, and alkali salts. It serves diverse purposes such as thickening agents, dispersants, flocculants, wetting agents, coatings, and textile finishes. Its reactivity with a wide array of organic and inorganic compounds makes it a valuable source material for producing various lower molecular weight compounds. For instance, through reactions with water, alcohols, amines, halogens, and chlorinated hydrocarbons, acrylic acid can generate derivatives of propionic a\\r\\n\\r\\ncid. Additionally, it participates in reactions leading to unsaturated fatty acids, heterocyclic compounds, and Diels-Alder addition products.\\r\\n\\r\\nDue to its tendency to explosively polymerize, acrylic acid requires stabilization using inhibitors like hydroquinone before shipping. Typically, there\'s no need to remove the stabilizer as its effect can be balanced by adding an excessive initiator.\",\"id\":\"Asam akrilik, yang dicirikan oleh struktur asam karboksilat tak jenuhnya (CH2=CHCO2H), berbentuk cairan bening dan tidak berbau. Asam akrilik menunjukkan ke